    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Political entities have a government in which the supreme rule is intended to be God or a god directly, or through a priestly order. Also, one whose government is heavily influenced by religious leaders.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000046455/Oxford Paperback Encyclopedia (1999)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000046352/Oxford English Reference Dictionary (1996)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Una forma de gobernar por Dios, directamente por un dios o a través de una orden sacerdotal. También, uno cuyo gobierno es fuertemente influenciado por líderes religiosos.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Een regeringsvorm waarbij God of een god zelf of via een priesterlijke orde regeert. Ook: regeringsvormen die in belangrijke mate worden beïnvloed door religieuze leiders.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000099099/Van Dale groot woordenboek (1994)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>政體形式的一種；由上帝或神直接或透過教士階層來掌控。此外，亦可指深受宗教領袖影響之政體。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
